{
  "id": "mcp/tools_list/basic",
  "mode": "mcp",
  "corpus": "multi-lang",
  "go_binary": "${LCI_GO}",
  "cpp_binary": "${LCI_CPP}",
  "invocation": {
    "args": ["mcp"],
    "stdin": "{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"tools/list\",\"params\":{}}",
    "cwd": "${CORPUS}"
  },
  "capture": ["stdout", "exit"],
  "parse": "json",
  "_pending": "DO_NOT_REGISTER_YET — FIX-D.2 (Option B emit-order) landed and key ordering is parity-correct, BUT tool DESCRIPTION TEXT diverges between Go and C++. Go's tool definitions carry richer text (emoji prefixes, expanded help, valid-value enumerations); C++ src/mcp/server.cpp + src/mcp/handlers_*.cpp registrations carry terser text. Discovered when registering this descriptor post-FIX-D.2: parity_runner reports ~20+ `stable mismatch` failures on result.tools[].description and result.tools[].inputSchema.properties.*.description — pure content diff, not ordering. Closing this descriptor requires FIX-D.3 (text-content sync across 14 tool registrations to match Go-side text byte-for-byte). Filed as fix subtask under loop AN8m7hohEdlM.",
  "_rationale": "FIX-D byte-equivalence descriptor. Two of three prerequisites landed: (1) stub dedup (FIX-D.1, commit 02594be) — registered_tools_ count matches Go's 14; (2) Option B custom emit-order (FIX-D.2) — src/mcp/server.cpp::handle_request tools/list branch builds envelope with nlohmann::ordered_json matching Go jsonschema-go field ordering (schema-root type→properties→required; per-property type→description; tool list alphabetical-by-name; tool object keys alphabetical [description, inputSchema, name]). Third prerequisite (FIX-D.3) outstanding: tool DESCRIPTION TEXT sync. Field-by-field audit in MODULE_MAP.md 'Decision: tools/list emit-order parity'.",
  "tiers": {
    "stable": [
      "result.content[].type"
    ],
    "_rationale_stable": "Until FIX-D.3 (text-content sync) lands, only the JSON-RPC envelope content type is byte-stable. The real assertion target is result.tools[] — held in ignore until text sync ships.",
    "ignore": [
      "result.tools"
    ],
    "_rationale_ignore": "result.tools is the body under test; held in ignore tier until FIX-D.3 (text sync) closes the content gap. After FIX-D.3 ships: move to stable, drop ignore entry, rename .pending → .parity.json. Expected post-fix shape per Go: 14 tools alphabetically ordered by name, each with top-level keys [description, inputSchema, name] (alpha), inputSchema with keys [type, properties, required] (insertion via jsonschema-go struct), properties map alphabetical, per-property keys [type, description] (insertion via jsonschema-go Property struct). The centralized JSON-RPC envelope ignore baseline already masks id/jsonrpc/result.meta.* — those don't need per-descriptor entries."
  },
  "tolerances": {
    "timed_max_ms": 60000
  },
  "expect_exit": 0
}
